{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "We conducted the automatic evaluation of the generated reports using language-based metrics and classification-based metrics 32.",
    "The languagebased metrics used in this study include BLEU, CIDEr, ROUGE, SPICE, and BERTScore.",
    "BLEU 33 is a widely used automatic metric for evaluating the quality of machine translations and scores by calculating the overlap of n-grams between the generated text and reference texts.",
    "An n-gram is a contiguous sequence of 'n' words from a given sample of text.",
    "Given that many ophthalmic terms are compound words often composed of up to four words, we calculated BLEU1, BLEU2, BLEU3, and BLEU4 as evaluation metrics."
  ],
